              "contentData": [
                {
                  "contentTypeKey": "dba6735d-7dc0-4fe4-b679-bb35d308181a",
                  "udi": "umb://element/a7cc27bbfa074584993221e0d2fd8bd5",
                  "answer": "<p><span class=\"-blue-text\"><strong>Application for loan of £247,500 at 90% LTV</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">The applicant had been a <strong>Production Manager for over six years with their current employer</strong> on a basic of £49,500, with no dependents and no commitments.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">Affordability was good, so we were happy to <strong>apply a loan to income multiple of 5x income.</strong></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong> </strong><span class=\"-blue-text\"><strong> </strong><strong>Application for loan of £480,000 at 56% LTV</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">The applicant had been a Risk Manager for <strong>over five years with their current employer</strong> on a <strong>basic of £81,500</strong> and <strong>received an annual bonus of £14,500 paid in the current tax year</strong>.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">To obtain the loan required we needed to <strong>apply a loan to income multiple of 5x income on 100% bonus.</strong> However, <strong>we only required 50% of the bonus to meet affordability</strong>, therefore we were happy to lend the amount required.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"-blue-text\"><strong> </strong><strong>Application for loan of £555,000 at 75% LTV</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">The applicant was an Investment Banker and had <strong>only received one bonus with their current employer</strong>, however, they <strong>had a track record of bonuses</strong> with previous employers.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">The current employer confirmed in writing that the applicant was expected to earn almost an extra £30k in bonus at the next payment date (double what they had currently earned).</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">Therefore, we were <strong>able to use this year’s bonus at 100%</strong> to support affordability and <strong>apply a loan to income multiple of 5x income.</strong></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"-blue-text\"><strong>Application for loan of £692,500 at 80% LTV</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">The applicant worked for a Private Equity firm and had <strong>only resided in the UK for 18 months</strong>, therefore <strong>only had one year’s bonus</strong> with the current employer.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">As we were able to get a <strong>meaningful credit score despite the limited residency in the UK</strong>, we were <strong>happy to take 50% of the applicants most recent bonus at 5x Income</strong>.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong> </strong><span class=\"-blue-text\"></span><span class=\"-blue-text\"></span><span class=\"-blue-text\"><strong>Application for loan of £1,295,000 at 85% LTV </strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">One of the applicants owned and <strong>ran a successful insurance company</strong>. They had decided to <strong>pay themselves low dividends and the keep cash in the company bank account</strong>. The size of loan they wanted wouldn’t have been possible under our standard loan terms as their assessable income (salary plus dividends) would have limited the loan we could offer.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">When reviewing the case we were able to use the <strong>average of the last two years’ net profit after tax (NPAT) and latest salary</strong> to achieve the loan amount required.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">Due to the excellent affordability status of the applicants we were able to<strong> apply a loan to income multiple of 5x their combined income</strong>; which is higher than our standard terms.</span></li>\n</ul>"
                }
              ],
              "settingsData": []
            }
          },
          {
            "contentTypeKey": "cc37be6c-af82-4a8f-bcfe-5dc50d675c4f",
            "udi": "umb://element/63555a5eec3e43759ae33a2acee8aec9",
            "question": "Interest Only",
            "answer": {
              "layout": {
                "Umbraco.BlockList": [
                  {
                    "contentUdi": "umb://element/8386f7d1dc5e4c38b46b4dff29bc4de2"
                  }
                ]
              },
              "contentData": [
                {
                  "contentTypeKey": "dba6735d-7dc0-4fe4-b679-bb35d308181a",
                  "udi": "umb://element/8386f7d1dc5e4c38b46b4dff29bc4de2",
                  "answer": "<p><span class=\"-blue-text\"><strong>Application for loan of £822,000 at 75% LTV </strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">Applicant one was an employed software engineer for seven years and applicant two was an employed director. They had a <strong>combined income of c£286,000</strong>. The applicants had <strong>used unsecured credit whilst undertaking home improvements</strong> and <strong>wanted to clear this as part of the remortgage.</strong></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">The <strong>applicants wanted a part repayment and part interest only mortgage</strong>. <strong>We agreed to lend 60% LTV on the interest only part</strong> and <strong>the remainder on capital and interest</strong> <strong>up until applicant two's 75th birthday.</strong></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"-blue-text\"><strong>Application for loan of £707,000 at 59% LTV </strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">The applicant had been employed as a Research Director for three years earning £166,000 and wanted to do a like for like remortgage.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">As the <strong>applicant’s occupation meant it was plausible to work until age 75</strong>, and they were <strong>going to downsize in five years’</strong> time <strong>we agreed to stress affordability on interest only and lend to age 75.</strong></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong> </strong></p>"
                }
              ],
              "settingsData": []
            }
          },
          {
            "contentTypeKey": "cc37be6c-af82-4a8f-bcfe-5dc50d675c4f",
            "udi": "umb://element/431bda12bd3a45d4bf5301cb57f594db",
            "question": "Residential ",
            "answer": {
              "layout": {
                "Umbraco.BlockList": [
                  {
                    "contentUdi": "umb://element/5a6ba588a15f42e492fbb617795c306f"
                  }
                ]
              },
              "contentData": [
                {
                  "contentTypeKey": "dba6735d-7dc0-4fe4-b679-bb35d308181a",
                  "udi": "umb://element/5a6ba588a15f42e492fbb617795c306f",
                  "answer": "<p><span class=\"-blue-text\"><strong>Application for a loan of £520,000 at 89% LTV </strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">Applicant one was a dentist with pre-settled status and had been self employed for two years. Applicant two had the permanent right to reside in the UK and was an employed scientist of 4 years. They had no dependents and a credit card payment of £65 per month.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">Applicant one’s first year’s <strong>income was impacted by Covid</strong> and therefore significantly lower than the latest year.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">Our s<strong>tandard criteria for pre-settled status applications are restricted to a maximum of 75% LTV</strong>. However, due to the strength of the application <strong>we agreed an exception</strong>.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">Also, the applicant could provide the last six months remittances slips which when annualised would mean the current tax year will be significantly higher. We were <strong>happy to use the latest year in isolation.</strong></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"-blue-text\"><strong>Application for a loan of £245,000 at 90% LTV  </strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">Sole applicant had been a <strong>self employed dentist for nine months</strong>. They were previously employed whilst completing their training. They had no dependents and no commitments.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">The applicant was <strong>purchasing a flat with a gifted deposit from parents overseas</strong>.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">As the applicant could provide remittance slips for the last nine month showing an upward trend, we were <strong>able to average and annualise the income</strong> and lend the loan required. </span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"-blue-text list-bullets\"><strong>Application for a loan of £822,000 at 75% LTV</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">Applicant one had been an employed software engineer for seven years and applicant two was an employed director. They had a combined income of c£286,000. The applicants had used unsecured credit whilst undertaking home improvements and want to clear this as part of the remortgage.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">The <strong>applicants wanted a part repayment and part interest only mortgage</strong>. <strong>We agreed to lend 60% LTV on the interest only part </strong>and <strong>the remainder on capital and interest up to applicant two's 75th birthday.</strong></span></li>\n</ul>"
                }
              ],
              "settingsData": []
            }
          },
          {
            "contentTypeKey": "cc37be6c-af82-4a8f-bcfe-5dc50d675c4f",
            "udi": "umb://element/aabd69d0817347d1b41499a3cd4f0ec4",
            "question": "Doctors and Locums",
            "answer": {
              "layout": {
                "Umbraco.BlockList": [
                  {
                    "contentUdi": "umb://element/739eccad99ca42f9a92c6528c5623634"
                  }
                ]
              },
              "contentData": [
                {
                  "contentTypeKey": "dba6735d-7dc0-4fe4-b679-bb35d308181a",
                  "udi": "umb://element/739eccad99ca42f9a92c6528c5623634",
                  "answer": "<p><span class=\"-blue-text\"><strong>Application for loan of 213,000 at 85% LTV</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">The applicant was <strong>about to become a partner in a GP practice</strong>. They’ve been employed with the practice for over three years and were guaranteed at least their basic salary in the first year. After that they would receive a profit share. </span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">Although the applicant was <strong>newly self employed</strong>, we were happy to <strong>proceed with the request based on the history of employment in the practice.</strong></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"-blue-text\"><strong>Application for loan of £259,250 at 85% LTV</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">The applicant was a doctor and had <strong>recently began a contract</strong> to cover a period of maternity leave. They’d only been contracting for three months at the point of application. </span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">Due to the nature of the contract <strong>we were aware that it may not be renewed but proceeded</strong> as proposed. This was because the <strong>underwriter was confident that an alternative contract/employment could be obtained</strong> at a similar level due to their profession and experience.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"-blue-text\"><strong>Application for loan of £564,000 at 75% LTV</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">The <strong>applicant was previously an employed GP</strong> but this ceased when they <strong>began self employed locum work</strong>. </span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">We obtained evidence of the income earned to date, as well as previous earnings, so <strong>annualised the locum income and used that for assessment.</strong></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"-blue-text\"><strong>Application for loan of £720,000 at 75% LTV</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">Applicant one was employed as a surgeon with the NHS and also completed private work through a limited company. Applicant two was employed as a practice manager in applicant one's company.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">We <strong>used the latest years’ net profit after tax figure (in addition to employed income)</strong> to calculate the assessable income.</span></li>\n</ul>"
                }
              ],
              "settingsData": []
            }
          },
          {
            "contentTypeKey": "cc37be6c-af82-4a8f-bcfe-5dc50d675c4f",
            "udi": "umb://element/11129f262ca042c7a1916531188156c5",
            "question": "Dentists",
            "answer": {
              "layout": {
                "Umbraco.BlockList": [
                  {
                    "contentUdi": "umb://element/319337dc58f9448a9eec7531f36662d8"
                  }
                ]
              },
              "contentData": [
                {
                  "contentTypeKey": "dba6735d-7dc0-4fe4-b679-bb35d308181a",
                  "udi": "umb://element/319337dc58f9448a9eec7531f36662d8",
                  "answer": "<p><span class=\"-blue-text\"><strong>Application for loan of £520,000 at 89% LTV </strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">Applicant one had been a self employed dentist for two years. Applicant two was an employed scientist for four years. They had no dependents and a credit card payment of £65 per month.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">Applicant one’s first year’s <strong>income was impacted by Covid</strong> and therefore <strong>significantly lower than the latest year.</strong></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">As the applicant could provide the last six remittances slips which when annualised would mean the current tax year will be significantly higher, we were <strong>happy to use the latest year in isolation.</strong></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"-blue-text\"><strong>Application for a loan of £245,000 at 90% LTV  </strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">Sole applicant had been a self employed dentist for nine months. They were previously employed whilst completing their training. They had no dependents and no commitments.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">The applicant was purchasing a flat with a gifted deposit from parents overseas.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">As the applicant could provide remittance slips for the last nine month showing an upward trend, <strong>we were able to average and annualise the income</strong> and lend the loan required. </span></li>\n</ul>"
                }
              ],
              "settingsData": []
            }
          },
          {
            "contentTypeKey": "cc37be6c-af82-4a8f-bcfe-5dc50d675c4f",
            "udi": "umb://element/b991e212bc7748f1b3296fe7f81554eb",
            "question": "Self employed equity partners",
            "answer": {
              "layout": {
                "Umbraco.BlockList": [
                  {
                    "contentUdi": "umb://element/f22caf5942b54b45a9d08a31fb9ad5b8"
                  }
                ]
              },
              "contentData": [
                {
                  "contentTypeKey": "dba6735d-7dc0-4fe4-b679-bb35d308181a",
                  "udi": "umb://element/f22caf5942b54b45a9d08a31fb9ad5b8",
                  "answer": "<p><span class=\"-blue-text\"><strong>Application for a loan of £500,000 at 50% LTV </strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">The applicant had been an <strong>employee of a limited liability partnership (LLP)</strong> for a few years and around 18 months ago <strong>became a self-employed partner in the firm</strong>. The LLP was well established and profitable.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">When reviewing the case we agreed to <strong>include the applicant’s profit share</strong> as we received confirmation from the finance director of the previous and expected earnings along with a P60 to evidence the level of earnings before becoming an equity partner.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"-blue-text\"><strong>Application for loan of 213,000 at 85% LTV</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">The applicant was about to become a partner in a GP practice. They have been employed with the practice for over three years and were guaranteed at least their basic salary in the first year. After that they would receive profit share.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"list-bullets\">Although the <strong>applicant was newly self employed</strong>, we were <strong>happy to proceed</strong> with the request <strong>based on the history of employment in the practice.</strong></span></li>\n</ul>"
                }
              ],
              "settingsData": []
            }
          }
        ],
        "settingsData": []
      }
    }
  ],
